article.headline: Long Island U. 90, Fairleigh Dickinson 77
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Jaytornah Waisseh scored 23 points and Kellen Allen had 22 to lead Long Island University to a 90-77 victory over Fairleigh Dickinson on Saturday. Eugene Kotrobai added 12 points for the Blackbirds (5-3, 1-1 Northeast Conference). Manny Ubilla had 22 of his 34 points in the first half and Sean Baptiste added 15 points and 12 rebounds for the Knights (1-5, 0-1), who lost their straight. LIU led 27-15 on a 3-pointer by Kyle Johnson with 8:45 left in the first half. FDU went on a 28-10 run that was capped by Baptiste's 3 with 1:23 to go that made it 43-37. The Knights led 43-41 at halftime. Waisseh made two free throws to start the Blackbirds' 21-4 run. Allen's layup with 7:26 to play capped the spurt and gave LIU a 72-58 lead.
